<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Request2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Request,</orth> vb. to ask, to beg, to demand: <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.474" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 474</bibl> (Qq <emph>as you r.,</emph> Ff <emph>at your r.</emph>). <bibl n="shak. ant 3.4.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 4, 24</bibl>. With an inf.: <cit><quote>she would r. to know your heaviness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1283" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1283</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 122</bibl>. With an accus. indicating the person asked, and an inf.: <cit><quote>did r. me to importune you,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.3.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 3, 13</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.2.102" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 2, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.9.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 9, 86</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.2.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 2, 40</bibl>. <cit><quote>to do more than she is --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.327" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 327</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>let me r. you off,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.7.127" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 7, 127</bibl></cit>. With an accus. indicating the thing demanded: <cit><quote>--s your company,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.3.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 3, 25</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.208" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 208</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.51" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 2, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 2, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 2, 56</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.133" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.2.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 2, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 1, 15</bibl>. <cit><quote>what he --s of us,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 32</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--s a parley of Lucius,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 4.4.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 4, 101</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>